reviews.review:
Huge Star Wars fan.  Bottom line, Im content with how things were resolved.

The effects were good, the acting wasnt terrible, not going to say this was a perfect movie, there were some unlikely twists that make you want to roll your eyes, but in the end the overall resolution was what I wanted and well done.  I will definitely be seeing this one more than once in the theater.
Best star wars  moving in the series
really the only complaint I have is that the ending could've been better. I am pretty young so I dont have the highest standards, but I think it was a great conclusion to the Skywalker saga.
A fitting end to a story that spanned 42 years and 9 movies. While not perfect it was very enjoyable.
Much better than the last one.

An electric, emotional, and fitting end to the Skywalker saga. Standout performances from Adam Driver and Daisy Ridley really sell the story beats and the arc of the film.  Plus the addition of fun new characters like Zori Bliss, Jannah, Babu Frik and Dio always make for a good time. 

I believe Director and Co-Screenwriter J.J. Abrams had a near impossible job to do in wrapping up this trilogy and saga and he stuck the landing in my view. Every major character (past and present) got their moment to shine. While it is not a perfect film, I loved how it danced with "The Last Jedi" and tied the bow on the sequel trilogy's major themes.
I liked the whole movie. I've been a star wars fan since 1977, and I have liked all of them. The new characters and plot lines were great. I' glad that she picked Skywalker as her last name.

This movies undoes Anakin's journey. They McGuffin everything. I mean I can't BELIEVE this is how we end this saga. They create new plot holes and you'll find yourself saying "what?" "Huh?" "How?" "That makes no sense" one word for this movie. TRAAAAAAAAAAASH

I enjoyed some parts of this movie, but the messy plot and HORRIBLE ENDING ruined any enjoyment I could have had watching this movie again and made me regret buying tickets to see it at all. BEN SOLO DESERVED BETTER ðŸ’”
